WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:12.512 --> 00:00:15.682 position:50% align:center
Pardon me. There's someone
I'm desperately seeking out.

00:00:15.765 --> 00:00:17.350 position:50% align:center
[YORKIST FOLLOWER A]
What do they look like?

00:00:17.434 --> 00:00:18.852 position:50% align:center
[HENRY]
He's pale, thin,

00:00:18.935 --> 00:00:20.979 position:50% align:center
and favors clothing
black as his hair.

00:00:21.062 --> 00:00:22.814 position:50% align:center
[YORKIST FOLLOWER B]
And his name?

00:00:22.897 --> 00:00:25.316 position:50% align:center
[HENRY]
His name?

00:00:25.400 --> 00:00:28.069 position:50% align:center
He goes by the name of Richard.

00:00:28.153 --> 00:00:29.988 position:50% align:center
[YORKIST FOLLOWER A]
Does he live around here?

00:00:30.071 --> 00:00:33.742 position:50% align:center
[HENRY] No. But I have
faith I'll find him.

00:00:33.825 --> 00:00:36.870 position:50% align:center
[RICHARD]
The taste. And scent of blood.

00:00:36.953 --> 00:00:42.375 position:50% align:center
So alike, the act of loving
yields them as well.

00:00:45.086 --> 00:00:48.131 position:50% align:center
[RICHARD chuckles]

00:00:49.382 --> 00:00:50.258 position:50% align:center
Uh, hey.

00:00:50.342 --> 00:00:52.218 position:50% align:center
Richard, you already drunk?

00:00:52.302 --> 00:00:55.513 position:50% align:center
[RICHARD]
A little. Or perhaps more.

00:00:55.597 --> 00:00:57.807 position:50% align:center
[RICHARD]
Everyone's the same.

00:00:57.891 --> 00:01:01.102 position:50% align:center
Once my real self is known,
they all take flight.

00:01:02.729 --> 00:01:06.316 position:50% align:center
[RICHARD] Only the battlefield
will ease my plight.

00:01:09.611 --> 00:01:11.488 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR]
York of the white rose,

00:01:11.571 --> 00:01:14.199 position:50% align:center
and Lancaster of the red.

00:01:14.282 --> 00:01:17.160 position:50% align:center
These royal houses with
their flowered crests

00:01:17.243 --> 00:01:19.954 position:50% align:center
have battled long and
hard for the throne.

00:01:20.038 --> 00:01:24.125 position:50% align:center
Nowadays, the people
refer to their strife as

00:01:24.209 --> 00:01:26.544 position:50% align:center
the "Wars of the Roses."

00:01:29.631 --> 00:01:34.636 position:50% align:center
